<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns:my="http://example.com/my" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_casm" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>casm</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>cans</orth></form><sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>петля (сети, башлыка, при тканье)</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>loop (of net, of bashlyk)</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>link</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>силок</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>snare</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>сеть</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>net</q></cit></sense></sense><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_casm." n=""><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>ficcag cans nilxij æj bunton</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>прежняя петля окончательно стянулась в узел</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the previous link finally pulled into a knot</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Sam."/><biblScope>64</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>kæd esti sæ cansi baftudæj, wæd bærgæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>если им что-либо попало в сеть, то хорошо</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>if they got anything in the net, then fine</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Bes._Ka_ke"/></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>ficcag cans nilxij æj bunton</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>прежняя петля окончательно стянулась в узел</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the previous link finally pulled into a knot</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Sam."/><biblScope>64</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>kæd esti sæ cansi baftudæj, wæd bærgæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>если им что-либо попало в сеть, то хорошо</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>if they got anything in the net, then fine</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Bes._Ka_ke"/></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>čašman-</w><gloss><q>глаз</q></gloss></mentioned>; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>časm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/><w>čöžm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/><w>čōm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/><w>cēm</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><w>cām</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>čašman-</w></mentioned>. Дальнейшие соответствия см. под <xr><ref target="#entry_cæst"/></xr> ‘глаз’. Идеосемантика ‘петля’←‘глаз’ обычна; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>глазок</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w>глаз</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>ячея сети</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>tvali</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>петля (сети, чулка)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>čašm</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>очко</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="en"><lang/><w>eye</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>петелька</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/><w>Auge</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fr"><lang/><w>oeil</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>петля</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fr"><w/><gloss><q>ушко</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/><w>a-bla</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>петля</q></gloss></mentioned> и др. В значении ‘глаз’ осетинский сохранил то же слово в несколько видоизмененном виде: <xr><ref target="#entry_cæst"/></xr>. Для соответствия <mentioned xml:lang="os-x-iron"><lang/><w>sm</w></mentioned> | <mentioned xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/><w>ns</w></mentioned> cp. <xr><ref target="#entry_sasm"/></xr> | %isans%i ‘клей’, <xr><ref target="#entry_fæsm"/></xr> | %ifans%i ‘шерсть’, <xr><ref target="#entry_fæzmyn"/></xr> | %ifænzun%i ‘подражать’, <xr><ref target="#entry_az"/></xr> | %ianz%i ‘год’. Иронский диалект сохраняет в этих случаях более старую форму.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope xml:lang="ru">17, 318, 361 прим., 379</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">17, 318, 361 footnote, 379</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_ИАН"><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1949, стр. 77</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1949, p. 77</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>čašman-</w><gloss><q>eye</q></gloss></mentioned>; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>časm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/><w>čöžm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/><w>čōm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/><w>cēm</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><w>cām</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>čašman-</w></mentioned>. See further correspondences under <xr><ref target="#entry_cæst"/></xr> ‘eye’. Ideosemantics ‘loop’←‘eye’ is usual; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>glazok</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w>glaz</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>mesh</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>tvali</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>mesh</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>čašm</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>hole</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="en"><lang/><w>eye</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>eyelet</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/><w>Auge</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>loop</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fr"><lang/><w>oeil</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>loop</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fr"><w/><gloss><q>eyelet</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/><w>a-bla</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>loop</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. Ossetic has kept the same word for 'eye' but it is modificated a little: <xr><ref target="#entry_cæst"/></xr>. For the correspondence<mentioned xml:lang="os-x-iron"><lang/><w>sm</w></mentioned> | <mentioned xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/><w>ns</w></mentioned> cf. <xr><ref target="#entry_sasm"/></xr> | %isans%i ‘glue’, <xr><ref target="#entry_fæsm"/></xr> | %ifans%i ‘wool’, <xr><ref target="#entry_fæzmyn"/></xr> | %ifænzun%i ‘mimic’, <xr><ref target="#entry_az"/></xr> | %ianz%i ‘year’. Iron dialect keeps a more old form in these cases.<bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope xml:lang="ru">17, 318, 361 прим., 379</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">17, 318, 361 footnote, 379</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_ИАН"><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1949, стр. 77</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1949, p. 77</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry>